00:00:22,314 --> 00:00:27,611
ALL THAT YOU POSSESS

2
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:13,551
This is where he threw himself under the train.

3
00:02:13,592 --> 00:02:15,386
April 14, 1979.

4
00:02:16,595 --> 00:02:18,180
He said the voices in his head

5
00:02:18,222 --> 00:02:20,599
wouldn't let him leave the tracks.

6
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:25,396
It's a miracle he survived.

7
00:02:25,437 --> 00:02:29,316
He sustained multiple injuries, and his right hand was shredded.

8
00:02:29,859 --> 00:02:31,819
When he woke up in the hospital,

9
00:02:31,861 --> 00:02:33,529
he couldn't remember who he was.

10
00:02:33,571 --> 00:02:36,198
Apparently, he was reciting French poetry.

11
00:02:37,408 --> 00:02:42,329
He was transferred to a psychiatric hospital in Warsaw

12
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:45,207
and then went to live with his mother in the country.

13
00:02:45,583 --> 00:02:50,170
That's where he wrote his book To Come to Terms with the World,

14
00:02:50,212 --> 00:02:52,298
with his left hand, of course.

15
00:02:53,299 --> 00:02:55,384
He never finished it.

16
00:02:56,468 --> 00:02:58,345
One day...

17
00:02:59,138 --> 00:03:02,182
he went to his apartment in Warsaw...

18
00:03:03,893 --> 00:03:05,895
and hanged himself.

19
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:17,967
You've reached Pierre Leduc.

20
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:20,344
Leave me a message and I'll call you back.

21
00:04:48,372 --> 00:04:50,791
"I FOUND MY DREAMS"

22
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,227
I FOUND MY DREAMS AGAIN

23
00:05:10,269 --> 00:05:11,979
THE DREAMS I ONCE PUT

24
00:05:12,021 --> 00:05:14,273
IN MY POCKET FULL OF HOLES

25
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:16,859
WHEN AT NIGHT AN ENORMOUS RAVEN

26
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:20,404
FLEW TO THE CLEAR RIVER, THE GOOD RIVER

27
00:05:27,202 --> 00:05:30,706
That night bats devoured all the stars

28
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,126
White butterflies

29
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:37,171
Only black butterflies remained

30
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:41,175
Truth became like the moon

31
00:05:41,216 --> 00:05:45,637
rolling over a smooth mirror for four weeks

32
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:08,118
So there you are.

33
00:06:10,204 --> 00:06:12,623
Everybody's been looking for you all week.

34
00:06:13,582 --> 00:06:15,292
I was in the country.

35
00:06:19,588 --> 00:06:21,131
What are you doing?

36
00:06:21,465 --> 00:06:23,133
I'm leaving.

37
00:06:23,509 --> 00:06:24,635
Where are you going?

38
00:06:24,676 --> 00:06:26,595
Nowhere. Home.

39
00:06:28,555 --> 00:06:29,723
I'm resigning.

40
00:06:29,765 --> 00:06:30,974
What?

41
00:06:31,016 --> 00:06:32,893
I'm leaving the university.

42
00:06:34,103 --> 00:06:37,022
I've got a bunch of boxes. Can you give me a ride?

43
00:06:39,441 --> 00:06:41,110
Will you finish your thesis?

44
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,654
What about your class?

45
00:06:43,695 --> 00:06:45,322
They'll get a replacement.

46
00:06:45,364 --> 00:06:47,074
A month before the term ends?

47
00:06:47,116 --> 00:06:49,910
- Listen, I can't do this anymore. - Do what?

48
00:06:49,952 --> 00:06:51,870
Any of it!

49
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:54,540
Teach students who can't read or write,

50
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,416
put up with faculty...

51
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:59,795
If I hear "collective agreement" or "lexical frequencies" once more,

52
00:06:59,837 --> 00:07:01,421
I'm going to hit someone.

53
00:07:05,384 --> 00:07:08,137
This isn't a literature department, for Christ's sake.

54
00:07:08,178 --> 00:07:09,972
It's an accounting firm.

55
00:07:19,982 --> 00:07:21,608
Pierre, what's going on?

56
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:23,277
I don't know.

57
00:07:23,694 --> 00:07:25,696
You could apply for sick leave.

58
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,489
I'm not sick.

59
00:07:32,536 --> 00:07:34,121
"AUTUMN"

60
00:07:34,163 --> 00:07:37,457
LOST, ENGULFED IN THE GARDENS OF RUST-RED AUTUMN

61
00:07:37,499 --> 00:07:41,628
TEARING OFF THE LEAVES ONE BY ONE LIKE THE HOURS OF EXISTENCE

62
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:29,426
You've reached Pierre Leduc.

63
00:08:29,468 --> 00:08:32,012
Leave me a message and I'll call you back.

64
00:08:35,557 --> 00:08:37,392
Pierre, it's your father.

65
00:08:37,434 --> 00:08:39,937
I've been trying to reach you for a week.

66
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:42,773
Call me back. It's important. Goodbye.

67
00:09:10,676 --> 00:09:14,638
Lost, engulfed

68
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:18,225
in the gardens of rust-red autumn

69
00:09:18,809 --> 00:09:21,270
tearing off the leaves one by one

70
00:09:22,521 --> 00:09:25,232
like the hours of existence

71
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,486
Going from tree to tree

72
00:09:29,987 --> 00:09:32,698
from pain back to pain

73
00:09:34,074 --> 00:09:36,743
A silent walk of suffering

74
00:09:37,369 --> 00:09:40,247
that does not awaken the sleeping wind

75
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:45,168
Tearing off the leaves with no regret

76
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:47,963
with a sad, warm smile

77
00:09:48,547 --> 00:09:50,549
Leaving the very last one

78
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:53,719
to someone else before dying

79
00:10:39,514 --> 00:10:40,849
You're leaving?

80
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:50,650
You have no idea what this does to me.

81
00:10:53,779 --> 00:10:57,324
You can't keep leaving and coming back.

82
00:10:59,618 --> 00:11:01,620
This has to stop.

83
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,206
But you're my only friend.

84
00:11:09,836 --> 00:11:11,588
I'm sorry.

85
00:11:35,445 --> 00:11:36,780
Pierre!

86
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:39,324
Your father wants to see you.

87
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:41,034
Get in.

88
00:11:42,202 --> 00:11:43,829
Get in!

89
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:56,049
Son of a bitch!

90
00:11:56,091 --> 00:11:58,802
You knew the balcony wasn't safe!

91
00:11:58,844 --> 00:12:01,680
A 5-year-old girl is in the hospital because of you!

92
00:12:01,721 --> 00:12:05,267
She might not ever walk again! Look at me, Leduc!

93
00:12:05,308 --> 00:12:08,520
If she doesn't get better, I'll see you in hell!

94
00:12:13,692 --> 00:12:15,485
Hello, Pierre.

95
00:12:18,864 --> 00:12:20,490
How's your mother?

96
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:24,619
How do you expect? Is that what you wanted to see me about?

97
00:12:26,955 --> 00:12:28,874
Would you like a coffee or something?

98
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:30,500
No, thanks.

99
00:12:30,834 --> 00:12:32,961
Get me a scotch, would you?

100
00:12:39,885 --> 00:12:41,845
Still at the university?

101
00:12:43,013 --> 00:12:44,723
Yes.

102
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:46,933
Still lecturing?

103
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:48,852
Yes.

104
00:12:54,191 --> 00:12:55,984
Have a seat.

105
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:11,958
Pierre, I'm dying. I have cancer.

106
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:14,503
It's spread everywhere.

107
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:18,089
The doctors don't give me three months.

108
00:13:18,632 --> 00:13:21,426
- There's nothing they can do? - Apparently not.

109
00:13:22,427 --> 00:13:24,012
I'm sorry.

110
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:29,059
I'm leaving the company to you.

111
00:13:29,476 --> 00:13:30,936
I don't want it.

112
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:34,231
You don't have to run it yourself.

113
00:13:35,357 --> 00:13:37,317
It's awful what you're going through.

114
00:13:37,359 --> 00:13:40,028
I'm sad for you. But I don't want that money.

115
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:43,156
- Why not? - Because it's dirty.

116
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:46,368
- What? - It's dirty money, Dad.

117
00:13:46,409 --> 00:13:48,787
You've been screwing people over for 40 years.

118
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:51,331
You screwed your employees and your partners.

119
00:13:51,373 --> 00:13:53,291
You bribed politicians.

120
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,628
You're a crook. You can't deny it.

121
00:13:57,462 --> 00:13:59,548
Do you know how much it's worth?

122
00:13:59,589 --> 00:14:00,966
I don't care.

123
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:03,426
Over $50 million.

124
00:14:03,885 --> 00:14:06,388
Do whatever you want with it. It's yours.

125
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:07,931
I won't take it.

126
00:14:07,973 --> 00:14:09,683
You're getting it anyway.

127
00:14:09,724 --> 00:14:11,560
I won't take it.

